This file is Claude Code's entry point. The two imports above pull in:

- `@AGENTS.md` — cross-tool agent conventions (also read by Cursor, Codex, Aider, Copilot).
- `@docs/team-constitution.md` — the ravenclaude-core team constitution (Team Lead pattern, dispatch playbook, Structured Output Protocol, Cited-Adjudicator Escalation). This file was copied into your repo at init time so it survives `/plugin marketplace update` and works for every contributor regardless of their Claude Code cache layout.

Anything below is **Claude-Code-specific** and is not meaningful to other agentic tools.

## Plan-mode default

For non-trivial changes touching more than two files, enter plan mode first and present a Keep / Update / Deny structure before writing.

## Plugin hooks active in this project

The `ravenclaude-core` plugin installs four hooks automatically:

- `format-on-write` (PostToolUse) — runs the appropriate formatter after every file edit.
- `guard-destructive` (PreToolUse / Bash) — blocks obviously destructive shell commands.
- `enforce-layout` (PreToolUse / Write|Edit|MultiEdit) — denies file writes that don't match `.repo-layout.json`.
- `remind-tests` (Stop) — reminds you to run the full test suite if source files changed.

To disable any of them, override in `.claude/settings.json`.

## Comfort-posture dashboard (Claude Code only)

`ravenclaude-core` ships an interactive **comfort-posture dashboard** — a point-and-click way to set Claude Code permission rules (deny / ask / allow, per category and per settings layer) and toggle the command-review tribunal (the Thing). It's a static, no-backend HTML page that ships **inside the installed plugin**, at the plugin cache root:

```
~/.claude/plugins/cache/ravenclaude/ravenclaude-core/<version>/dashboard.html
```

(On Windows: the equivalent path under your user profile's `.claude/plugins/cache`.) Open that file in any browser — it needs no server. Make your choices, then use the page's **Copy** / **Download** button to put the generated YAML into `.ravenclaude/comfort-posture.yaml`, and run `/set-posture` to translate it into `settings.json` permission rules. (On Claude Code on the web, the `reapply-posture` SessionStart hook re-applies a committed posture automatically.)

> **Cross-tool note:** the dashboard, comfort-posture, and the command-review tribunal are **Claude-Code-specific** — they work through Claude Code's `settings.json` permissions and PreToolUse hooks. Cursor, Codex, Aider, and GitHub Copilot do **not** execute them, so opening the dashboard there has no effect on those tools.

## Memory

User-scoped memory lives under `~/.claude/projects/`. Update `MEMORY.md` when something durable about the user, project, or working style changes.
